rf:recipe_04 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "004" ;
    rf:command "`just lint`" ;
    rf:purpose "`cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings` — **root `ggen` package only**, not `--workspace`; confirmed 2026-07-17 (`Checking` output names exactly one package). Real, untriaged debt exists in other crates once `--workspace` is added — see the `lint:` recipe's own comment in `justfile`" ;
    rf:timeout "180s" .

rf:recipe_05 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "005" ;
    rf:command "`just pre-commit`" ;
    rf:purpose "`fmt-check` → `check` → `lint` → `test-lib` → `coherence-check` → `guard-process-intelligence-boundary` → `guard-cheat-scan` → `guard-claims-schema` → `guard-pack-proofs` → `guard-generation-hash-pin` (10 gates; confirmed 2026-07-20 against the justfile's own `pre-commit:` dependency line — `guard-generation-hash-pin` validates the generation ledger's hash pins, appended 2026-07-20; do not trust a shorter step count from an older doc; `guard-pack-proofs` re-syncs + re-tests `examples/receiptctl`, making the generated pack proofs a repo-state-checkable gate). `guard-cheat-scan` currently fails on ~464 pre-existing test-quality findings (tracked as TECH-DEBT-001 in `docs/jira/2026-07-17-JTBD-VERIFICATION-DISCOVERED-BUGS.md`) — a real, tracked-not-fixed failure, not a regression" ;
    rf:timeout "<2min" .

rf:recipe_06 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "006" ;
    rf:command "`just slo-check`" ;
    rf:purpose "Performance SLOs — real wall-clock `date +%s` deltas around `cargo test -p ggen-engine --test receipt_chain_e2e` (180s threshold) plus a `cargo bench` startup check; see the `slo-check` recipe in `justfile`" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:recipe_07 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "007" ;
    rf:command "`just audit`" ;
    rf:purpose "Security vulnerabilities scan" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:recipe_08 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "008" ;
    rf:command "`just doc`" ;
    rf:purpose "Build HTML docs into `target/doc/`" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:recipe_09 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "009" ;
    rf:command "`just test-doc`" ;
    rf:purpose "Validate all `# Examples` blocks compile/run" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:recipe_10 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "010" ;
    rf:command "`just bench`" ;
    rf:purpose "`cargo bench` — **root `ggen` package only** (same scoping as `lint`; the root package does have 12 real `[[bench]]` entries, so this isn't a no-op, but it doesn't reach `ggen-engine`'s or other crates' benches). `just slo-check` separately targets the one bench that matters for the SLO gate (`cli_startup_performance`, which does live in the root package)" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:recipe_11 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "011" ;
    rf:command "`just sync`" ;
    rf:purpose "Runs `ggen sync --audit true` — **currently broken**: the live `sync run` verb (`crates/ggen-engine/src/verbs/sync.rs`) has no `--audit` flag (only `--dry-run`/`--watch`); confirmed 2026-07-17 by running the recipe (`error: unexpected argument '--audit' found`, exit 1)" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:recipe_12 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "012" ;
    rf:command "`just sync-dry`" ;
    rf:purpose "Runs `ggen sync --dry_run true` — **currently broken**: `--dry-run`/`--dry_run` is a bare switch on the live verb, it does not take a `true` value; confirmed 2026-07-17 by running the recipe (`error: unexpected argument 'true' found`, exit 1). Use `ggen sync run --dry-run` directly instead" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:recipe_13 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "013" ;
    rf:command "`ggen graph validate` / `ggen law validate`" ;
    rf:purpose "SHACL / law validation — there is no bare `ggen validate` noun (confirmed: `error: unrecognized subcommand 'validate'`); see `crates/ggen-engine/src/verbs/{graph.rs,law.rs}`" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:recipe_14 a rf:Recipe ;
    rf:order "014" ;
    rf:command "`ggen receipt verify`" ;
    rf:purpose "Verify the BLAKE3 chain hash of the current sync receipt — **zero arguments**; always targets `.ggen-v2/receipt.json` under the resolved project root (`crates/ggen-engine/src/verbs/receipt.rs`)" ;
    rf:timeout "-" .

rf:diag_01 a rf:DiagnosticCode ;
    rf:order "001" ;
    rf:code "**GGEN-TPL-001**" ;
    rf:surface "SPARQL ↔ Tera" ;
    rf:severity "ERROR" ;
    rf:meaning "Template consumes `{{ var }}` that SELECT does not produce." ;
    rf:owner "`ggen-lsp/src/analyzers/tera_analyzer.rs`" .

rf:diag_02 a rf:DiagnosticCode ;
    rf:order "002" ;
    rf:code "**GGEN-OUT-001**" ;
    rf:surface "SPARQL ↔ ggen.toml" ;
    rf:severity "ERROR" ;
    rf:meaning "`output_file` pattern consumes unbound variable." ;
    rf:owner "`ggen-lsp/src/analyzers/tera_analyzer.rs`" .

rf:diag_03 a rf:DiagnosticCode ;
    rf:order "003" ;
    rf:code "**GGEN-YIELD-001**" ;
    rf:surface "ggen.toml ↔ OS" ;
    rf:severity "ERROR" ;
    rf:meaning "`output_file` escapes the project root (Layer Violation)." ;
    rf:owner "`ggen-lsp/src/analyzers/tera_analyzer.rs`" .

rf:diag_04 a rf:DiagnosticCode ;
    rf:order "004" ;
    rf:code "**GGEN-RULE-001**" ;
    rf:surface "ggen.toml ↔ OS" ;
    rf:severity "ERROR" ;
    rf:meaning "`{file = ...}` binding points at a missing file." ;
    rf:owner "`ggen-lsp/src/analyzers/tera_analyzer.rs`" .

rf:diag_05 a rf:DiagnosticCode ;
    rf:order "005" ;
    rf:code "**GGEN-QUERY-002**" ;
    rf:surface "SPARQL" ;
    rf:severity "WARNING" ;
    rf:meaning "`SELECT *` used (disables provision checks)." ;
    rf:owner "`ggen-lsp/src/analyzers/tera_analyzer.rs`" .

rf:diag_06 a rf:DiagnosticCode ;
    rf:order "006" ;
    rf:code "**E0011 / E0013**" ;
    rf:surface "SPARQL" ;
    rf:severity "WARNING*" ;
    rf:meaning "`CONSTRUCT` / `SELECT` lacks `ORDER BY` (Strict Mode: ERROR)." ;
    rf:owner "`ggen-lsp/src/analyzers/sparql_analyzer.rs` (author-time) **and** `ggen-config/src/manifest/validation.rs` (sync-time hard error; two independent implementations, not shared)" .

rf:diag_07 a rf:DiagnosticCode ;
    rf:order "007" ;
    rf:code "**E0015**" ;
    rf:surface "SPARQL" ;
    rf:severity "WARNING" ;
    rf:meaning "Identity `CONSTRUCT` detected (no-op mapping) — actively emitted, not reserved." ;
    rf:owner "`ggen-lsp/src/analyzers/sparql_analyzer.rs`" .

rf:arch_01 a rf:ArchSection ;
    rf:order "001" ;
    rf:sid "intro-and-codegen-core" ;
    rf:text "Full public API surface derived from LSP `documentSymbol` sweep of all workspace crates.\n\nUse LSP for navigation -- this file is orientation, not a substitute for `LSP workspaceSymbol`.\n\n## Crate Map (17 workspace members)\n\nRe-verified against `Cargo.toml` `members = [...]` on 2026-07-17 (16 array entries + the root\n`ggen` package = 17 total; `grep -c '^  \"crates/' Cargo.toml` → 16 — this exact count was\npreviously mis-stated in this file as 15/16 total; the miscount traced to `ggen-cheat-scanner`,\nadded by PR #257, never having been added to any table here — it now has its own row in the\nTesting infrastructure section below). The prior 12-member count (2026-07-16) is superseded: PR\n#255 (absolute-local-path Cargo dependency cleanup) added 4 more members — `powl2-decompose`,\n`chicago-tdd-tools` (+ its `chicago-tdd-tools/proc_macros` path-dependency, not itself a\ntop-level workspace member), `bcinr-pddl`, `bcinr-mfw-ir` — all `publish = false`, vendored to\neliminate `path = \"/Users/sac/...\"` dependencies that only resolved on one machine and broke CI\n(`cargo build --workspace` failing with \"No such file or directory\" for anyone else). See the\nPraxis kernel and Testing infrastructure sections below. Use `LSP workspaceSymbol` for live\nsymbol discovery — this table is orientation only. See `CRATE_CONSOLIDATION_ANALYSIS_2026-07-01.md`\nfor the 2026-07 pass's evidence base and phase-by-phase history.\n\n### Code generation core\n\n`ggen-core` is **fully deleted, not merely disconnected.** PR #255 (2026-07-16/17) first ported\nevery dependent off it and moved it from `[workspace] members` to root `Cargo.toml`'s `exclude`\nas an interim step; PR #259 (2026-07-17, \"remove ggen-core, rewrite README from first\nprinciples\") then deleted `crates/ggen-core/` outright. That interim \"excluded but present on\ndisk\" state — described at length in an earlier version of this note, including a 3-way\nstandalone-compile-failure demonstration — no longer exists and cannot be reproduced:\n`crates/ggen-core/` is absent from disk (`find crates -maxdepth 1 -iname 'ggen-core*'` → empty),\nand root `Cargo.toml`'s `exclude` list contains only `examples/7-agent-validation`. The\nexperimental, default-off `ggen wizard`/`sigma` commands (and `inverse_sync`), which used to\nimport now-nonexistent `ggen_core::` symbols, were deleted in the same pass rather than\nre-pointed — see `crates/ggen-cli/src/cmds/mod.rs`'s \"REMOVED\" comments and\n`docs/jira/v26.7.16/14-GGEN-CORE-REMOVAL-PROPOSAL.md` (marked superseded/executed). `ggen-engine`\nis the sole live half of this split." .

rf:arch_02 a rf:ArchSection ;
    rf:order "002" ;
    rf:sid "two-schemas-and-praxis" ;
    rf:text "### ggen.toml has two schemas\n\n`ggen.toml` is parsed by one of two independently-defined, incompatible struct hierarchies,\nchosen by a raw-text pre-parse before any typed parse runs: `ggen_engine::generation_rules::\nhas_generation_rules` (`crates/ggen-engine/src/generation_rules.rs:108`) checks the raw TOML for\na non-empty `[[generation.rules]]` array. If present, `sync()`'s Stage 0 dispatch\n(`crates/ggen-engine/src/sync.rs:155`) parses the file as `ggen_config::manifest::GgenManifest`\n(`crates/ggen-config/src/manifest/types.rs:160`, the \"declarative-rules\" schema) — `[[packs]]` is\nan array-of-tables of a flat `PackRef { name, registry, path, version }`. If absent, it falls\nthrough to `ggen_engine::config::GgenConfig` (`crates/ggen-engine/src/config.rs:45`, the\n\"frontmatter\" schema) — `[packs]` is instead a table-of-tables (`BTreeMap<String, PackRef>`) of\nan untagged `PackRef` enum, `Path { path, .. } | Git { .. }`. Same table names throughout\n(`[project]`, `[ontology]`, `[packs]`, `[templates]`, `[law]`), genuinely divergent shapes, and\nno automated cross-drift guard between the two.\n\n### Praxis kernel (ggen-engine's direct dependencies)\n\nVendored alongside `ggen-engine` in the same migration pass — renamed copies of\n`~/praxis/crates/{praxis-core,praxis-graphlaw}`. Both `publish = false`.\n\n**Correction (2026-07-17, PR #255, verified live) — supersedes the prior \"assume it reaches\n`~/praxis`\" correction below:** every absolute `path = \"/Users/sac/...\"` Cargo dependency in this\nworkspace was found and removed. `praxis-core`'s `arazzo.rs` module (the sole consumer of the\n`powl2-decompose`/`wasm4pm-arazzo` path deps this note used to describe) was deleted outright —\nconfirmed unused by any downstream crate (`ggen-engine`, `ggen-cli`) before removal; its dead\n`chatman-common`-gated `signing` feature/module went with it. `ArazzoProjectionReceipt` is no\nlonger part of `praxis-core`'s public API — the table row below is corrected accordingly.\n`praxis-graphlaw`'s own `powl2-decompose` dependency (genuinely load-bearing, reachable from\n`ggen-engine` via `chatman/{closure,abi,powl_projection,engine}.rs`) is now satisfied by the new\n`crates/powl2-decompose` workspace member (vendored, not a live path back to `~/praxis`) rather\nthan an absolute path — see that row below. `cargo fmt --all`'s crash (the consequence this note\nused to warn about) is resolved as a side effect: nothing in this workspace's manifest graph\nreaches outside `/Users/sac/ggen` anymore. Verify via `grep -rn 'path.*=.*\"/Users/sac'\n--include=\"Cargo.toml\" .` → empty." .

